<projectDesc><p>This transcription was made by Roderic Mullen and colleagues on the International Greek New Testament Project working towards an Electronic Edition of the Gospel According to John in the Byzantine Tradition, first published in 2007.</p></projectDesc>
<editorialDecl><p>The initial transcription file was a plain text file for use with COLLATE, later converted to XML. Further information about the transcription procedures followed may be found in the electronic edition at <ptr target="http://www.iohannes.com/byzantine/"/></p>

<p>The plain text file was converted to XML by Hugh Houghton and Catherine Smith using the project's Python conversion scripts 1.0.</p>
<p>The XML specifications used are version 1.4 of the IGNTP Guidelines available at <ptr target="http://epapers.bham.ac.uk/1727/"/></p>
<p>The original plain text header reads as follows: Status:G-A 565 (St. Petersburg Gr.53) John supplement begins Folio 389Transcribed by: RLMTranscription begun: 27.05.03Transcription finished: 29.05.03Transference to Collate by: RLMTransference to Collate begun: 27.05.03Transference to Collate finished: 29.05.03File date  and time:Placed in Level1: RLMLevel1 file date  and time: 29.05.03Placed in Level2:Placed in Level2 by: RLMLevel2 file date  and time: 12.06.03These files were  compared and differences resolved by: RLM-CJSPlaced in  Level3:Placed in  Level3 by:Notes: F 36 has marginal notesFr 191 is evidence that ms has been trimmed at top illustration of Luke seems later than othersFv 405 seems to have colophon, but it is very hard to read from the film\Fv 398 -Fr 405 are badly filmedback flyleaf is in very late hand --Fr 406 has John 1.1-17 and Fv 406 has John 20.19-26  -- this folio should be counted as another manuscriptFinal transcription file date  and time:    </p></editorialDecl>
